There are 5 ways to separate digits of an integer in python:


Method 1: Use str() and int() Function in List Comprehension

number = 56712
digits = [int(i) for i in str(number)]
print(number)


Method 2: Use str() Function With map()

number = 56712
digits = list(map(int,str(number)))
print(digits)


Method 3: Use Simple for Loop

number = 56712
string=str(number)
array=[]
for items in string:
  array.append(int(items))
print(array)


Method 4: Use math.ceil() With math.log() Function

import maths
number=56712
i=math.log(number,10)
j=math.ceil(i)
k=[integer//(10**i))%10 for i in range(j-1,-1,-1)]
print(k)


Method 5: Use divmod() Function

number=56712
array=[]
while number>0:
  number,remainder=divmod(number,10)
  array.append(remainder)
print(array)



